Secondly faith; ſhould a man leane himſelfe upon2. God, and upon Chriſt, ſhould a man apply all the promiſes of the Goſpell to his ſoule, and beleeve all that's contained in the covenant of grace; alas what of all this? if this man be dead ſtill, without ſuch a faith as produces life; it is little better then nothing; as Chriſt ſayes, He that lives and beleeves in me, Joh. 11. 26. true faith carries life with it, whereſoever it is; and therefore if a mans faith be without life, it is but equivocall faith. faith it may well be, But true faith it cannot be; for if thou wouldſt be able to ſay thou beleeveſt in Jeſus Chriſt, thou muſt be able to ſay that thou liveſt too in him; it's impoſſible a man ſhould rightly beleeve in Chriſt and be dead; 

                     •
                  o, he lives that beleeves in me, ſayes Chriſt.
